UNITED STATES of America v. Sewell Paul BAIRD, Appellant. No. 8740. Circuit Court of Appeals, Third Circuit. Argued Feb. 15, 1945. Decided Feb. 15, 1945. Anthony A. Calandra, of Newark, N. J., for appellant. Charles A. Stanziale, Asst. U. S. Atty., of Newark, N. J. (Thorn Lord, U. S. Atty., of Newark, N. J., on the brief), for appellee.

Before PARKER, MARIS, and GOODRICH, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The judgment of the District Court1 is affirmed.

No opinion for publication.
